will not stand to receive a single blow. Even Ahab is a braver thing—a nobler 
thing than that. Would now the wind but had a body; but all the things that 
most exasperate and outrage mortal man, all these things are bodiless, but only 
bodiless as objects, not as agents. There’s a most special, a most cunning, 
